description: Initially launched by Die Cast Machine Tools Ltd (DCMT) as a tie in to their Lone Star toy range, Lone Star Magazine was subsequently bought by Atlas Publishing. It ran for a decade and around 100 issues, before cancelling in 1962. As well as starring the Lone Star Rider, it also featured pirate strip Captain Cutlass and space hero Ace Hart, who was renamed Space Ace with the magazine's third issue to avoid confusion with Foldes Press' space hero Ace Hart.

description:
In 1958 Odhams Press split their licensed title Mickey Mouse Weekly into two comics. One, Walt Disney's Mickey Mouse, continued to carry the Disney related strips, while the other, Zip, took the non-Disney strips. Zip was launched by Odhams Press on 4th January 1958 with the initial strips including the cover star Skippy, Don Lawrence's Western strip Wells Fargo, Gerry Embleton's Robin Hood-esque Strongbow the Mighty (which Gerry's brother, Ron, had previously drawn for Mickey Mouse Weekly), and Harry Bishop's Tarna the Jungle Boy.

Zip lasted for 85 issues before being cancelled and merged into Swift.
name: Zip
